        "jobExcerpt": "Apptio, an IBM company, is the leading technology spend and value management software provider. Its AI-powered data insights empower leaders to make smarter financial and operational decisions. A pioneer and category leader in Technology Business Management (TBM) and FinOps, Apptio works with thousands of customers, partners, and community members worldwide. Responsible for achieving customer introductions&#8230;",
        "jobDescription": "<p>Apptio, an IBM company, is the leading technology spend and value management software provider. Its AI-powered data insights empower leaders to make smarter financial and operational decisions. A pioneer and category leader in Technology Business Management (TBM) and FinOps, Apptio works with thousands of customers, partners, and community members worldwide.</p>\n<p>Responsible for achieving customer introductions that lead to sales and represent Apptio products and services to partners that our joint offerings developed with prioritized focus partners. The Channel &amp; Alliances Manager must have a background selling software solutions, effective channel recruitment, and enablement strategies, conducting in-person sales calls and having a history of educating channel partners to achieve success. The role will involve driving pre-developed GTM’s with our Partners as well as driving enabling new IBM business partners to build TBM, FinOps and Agile practices.</p>\n<p><strong>You will drive GTM initiatives and activities with all of Apptio’s partners and select IBM business partners, including:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Apptio business partners focused on TBM, FinOps and Enterprise Agile Management</li>\n<li>IBM business partners focused initially on FinOps and extending to TBM and Agile over time</li>\n<li>IBM Value added distributors</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In addition, you will be responsible for recruiting, onboarding, managing, and developing and driving business plans with regional business partners in your territory including AWS ISV partners.</p>\n<h2>Responsibilities:</h2>\n<p>The Channels and Alliances Director must be able to develop and maintain senior and deep partner relations for the purpose of driving joint:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New logo deals and top of funnel leads</li>\n<li>Practice Development – build FinOps, TBM and Enterprise Agile practices in key partners</li>\n<li>Strong, sustained marketing programs, campaigns and events</li>\n<li>Establish customer success, value and expansion through planting partners as a core part of a customer deliver</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This role will report into the Regional VP, EMEA Channels and Alliances and work closely with a Snr Director of Alliances who will own the overall success of the DACH territory, EMEA Sales, Partner Marketing and Services teams. Focusing on Partner Planning, Business Development, Enablement, Go-to-Markets, Partner Lead Generation, Partner Campaign Creation, Sales Opportunity Management and Service Delivery. This role will interface closely to Regional Vice Presidents and Strategic Sales Leaders across the DACH region</p>\n<h2>Qualifications:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&#8217;s degree or equivalent with proven success in channel sales, extensive experience in enterprise software and a background in a SaaS based company</li>\n<li>MBA or other advanced degree would be beneficial</li>\n<li>An extensive network of channel partners within the assigned territory</li>\n<li>Documented success of bringing new channel partners to an organization</li>\n<li>Proof of quota attainment and meeting performance objectives</li>\n<li>Worked previously for a SaaS based software company</li>\n<li>Talented cross-functional collaborator able to develop trusted relationships and rapport</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills, including the ability to exercise assertiveness to influence others to create desired sales results</li>\n<li>Strong initiative, organization and prioritization skills with the proven ability to work in a self-directed environment</li>\n<li>Flexible, innovative, and able to respond appropriately in a time-critical environment</li>\n<li>Excellent presentation skills</li>\n<li>Ability to travel up to 50% of the time</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>A minimum of three years of demonstrated experience in working with similar companies as below or preferably direct experience:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>DACH Partner examples:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Integres/TimetoAct</li>\n<li>Crayon/Bechtle</li>\n<li>SoftwareOne/Liquid Reply</li>\n<li>Trustmarque/Ingram</li>\n<li>Arrow/TD Synnex</li>\n<li>Nanga Systems/Detecon</li>\n<li>Amasol/MHP</li>\n</ul>",
