        "jobExcerpt": "The work you’ll do as a contractor under a Deloitte Project Team includes working mainly on Dynatrace and other APM tools to onboard and define monitoring metrics for applications of all types. Key Responsibilities as a Contractor: Collaborate with software development groups to ensure operational needs are adequately considered and baked into the APM tool as&#8230;",
        "jobDescription": "<p>The work you’ll do as a contractor under a Deloitte Project Team includes working mainly on Dynatrace and other APM tools to onboard and define monitoring metrics for applications of all types.</p>\n<h2><strong>Key Responsibilities as a Contractor:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Collaborate with software development groups to ensure operational needs are adequately considered and baked into the APM tool as well as in new software releases.</li>\n<li>Define monitoring &amp; alarming thresholds. Setup clear and accurate SLO/SLI for efficient service monitoring</li>\n<li>Develop infrastructure (network, compute, storage) &amp; application capacity models.</li>\n<li>Drive toward automated deployments &amp; modern approaches to configuration management.</li>\n<li>Focus on application reliability. Ensure applications and infrastructure designs to avoid pitfalls of large scale SaaS offerings (bottlenecks, single points of failure, etc.).</li>\n<li>Full service handling (analysis, debugging, response, and resolution) of application level issues using Dynatrace or other application monitoring tool.</li>\n<li>Focus on service availability. Reduce MTTR by assisting the incident command, operations, and application developer teams to diagnose &amp; resolve service outages (incidents with significant customer impact).</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Qualifications:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Previous hands on experience on application and infra monitoring using advanced tools (mainly Dynatrace)</li>\n<li>Site reliability engineering experience including application performance observability, SLO/SLI establishments along with EB</li>\n<li>Being an APM expert is a must have skill for this role</li>\n<li>Experience working on SRE team that focused on application level monitoring, code level debugging, self-healing via automation and root cause analysis.</li>\n<li>Bachelor&#8217;s degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Candidates interested in applying for this opportunity must be geographically based in the United States </strong><strong>and must be legally authorized to work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship</strong></p>\n<p><strong>We do not accept agency resumes and are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Deloitte is not the employer for this role. This work is contracted through a third-party whose employees provides services to Deloitte.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>The expected pay range for this contract assignment is $80 to $100 per hour. </strong><strong>The exact pay rate will vary based on skills, experience, and location and will be determined by the third-party whose employees provide services to Deloitte.</strong></p>",
